---
import DocsLayout from '@/layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---
<DocsLayout
  title="GitHub Actions"
  description="Generate a ready-to-use GitHub Actions workflow for building and deploying your app with Shuttle."
  section="ci"
>
  <p>
    Run <code>shuttle ci generate --provider github</code> to generate a GitHub Actions workflow
    at <code>.github/workflows/shuttle-deploy.yml</code>. The workflow has two jobs:
    <strong>build</strong> (Docker build + registry push) and <strong>deploy</strong> (SSH into
    the server and call <code>shuttle deploy --skip-build</code>).
  </p>

  <h2>Generate the workflow</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle ci generate --provider github

# With options
shuttle ci generate \
  --provider github \
  --registry ghcr \        # ghcr (default) or docker-hub
  --branch main \          # trigger branch (default: main)
  --app my-app             # app name (defaults to shuttle.yml app name)
</code></pre>
  <p>
    The command writes the workflow file and prints the required secrets you need to configure in
    GitHub repository settings.
  </p>

  <h2>Generated workflow (GHCR)</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">name: Deploy my-app

on:
  push:
    branches: [main]

permissions:
  contents: read
  packages: write

jobs:
  build:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    outputs:
      image-tag: $&#123;&#123; steps.meta.outputs.tags &#125;&#125;
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Set up Docker Buildx
        uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@v3

      - name: Login to registry
        uses: docker/login-action@v3
        with:
          registry: ghcr.io
          username: $&#123;&#123; github.actor &#125;&#125;
          password: $&#123;&#123; secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN &#125;&#125;

      - name: Build and push
        uses: docker/build-push-action@v6
        with:
          context: .
          push: true
          tags: |
            ghcr.io/$&#123;&#123; github.repository &#125;&#125;:latest
            ghcr.io/$&#123;&#123; github.repository &#125;&#125;:$&#123;&#123; github.sha &#125;&#125;
          cache-from: type=gha
          cache-to: type=gha,mode=max

  deploy:
    needs: build
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - name: Deploy via SSH
        uses: appleboy/ssh-action@v1
        with:
          host: $&#123;&#123; secrets.DEPLOY_HOST &#125;&#125;
          username: $&#123;&#123; secrets.DEPLOY_USER &#125;&#125;
          key: $&#123;&#123; secrets.DEPLOY_SSH_KEY &#125;&#125;
          script: |
            shuttle deploy --skip-build --image ghcr.io/$&#123;&#123; github.repository &#125;&#125;:$&#123;&#123; github.sha &#125;&#125;
</code></pre>

  <h2>Required repository secrets</h2>
  <p>
    Configure these in <strong>Settings &rarr; Secrets and variables &rarr; Actions</strong>:
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Secret</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>DEPLOY_HOST</code></td>
        <td>Server IP address or hostname</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>DEPLOY_USER</code></td>
        <td>SSH username (e.g., <code>deploy</code>)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>DEPLOY_SSH_KEY</code></td>
        <td>SSH private key (contents of <code>~/.ssh/id_ed25519</code>)</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>
    <code>GITHUB_TOKEN</code> is provided automatically by GitHub Actions for GHCR authentication.
    No additional secret is needed for GHCR.
  </p>

  <h2>Docker Hub variant</h2>
  <p>
    Generate with <code>--registry docker-hub</code> to use Docker Hub instead of GHCR:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle ci generate --provider github --registry docker-hub
</code></pre>
  <p>
    Two additional secrets are required:
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Secret</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>DOCKERHUB_USERNAME</code></td>
        <td>Docker Hub username</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>DOCKERHUB_TOKEN</code></td>
        <td>Docker Hub access token (from hub.docker.com/settings/security)</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Secrets key in CI</h2>
  <p>
    If you use Shuttle's encrypted secrets, the <code>.shuttle/key</code> file must be available
    on the server before <code>shuttle deploy</code> runs. The typical approach is to copy the
    key during provisioning and never store it in CI. Alternatively, store it as a CI secret and
    restore it on the server during the deploy step:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">- name: Deploy via SSH
  uses: appleboy/ssh-action@v1
  with:
    host: $&#123;&#123; secrets.DEPLOY_HOST &#125;&#125;
    username: $&#123;&#123; secrets.DEPLOY_USER &#125;&#125;
    key: $&#123;&#123; secrets.DEPLOY_SSH_KEY &#125;&#125;
    script: |
      mkdir -p ~/.shuttle
      echo "$SHUTTLE_KEY" &gt; ~/.shuttle/key
      chmod 600 ~/.shuttle/key
      shuttle deploy --skip-build
  env:
    SHUTTLE_KEY: $&#123;&#123; secrets.SHUTTLE_KEY &#125;&#125;
</code></pre>
</DocsLayout>
